ing can address the noted weaknesses.\n**Open question:** Does any agent have additional positive information on Candidate\u202fB\u2019s or Candidate\u202fD\u2019s teamwork or communication abilities that has not yet been shared?\n**Conclusion & vote:** I consider **Candidate\u202fC** the most suitable overall for the long\u2011distance pilot position.\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_1\", \"vote\": \"Candidate C\"}", "thoughts": "We are agent_1. We have just asked agent_2 for info on D's teamwork, got answer: no info. Now we need to produce our public contribution. We should summarize all candidates, weigh, maybe ask any missing info. We have already asked about teamwork for A, B, C, D. We have no positive teamwork info for A, B, D. For C we have positive atmosphere. We have reliability for B, conscientiousness for C, leadership for A, responsibility for D. Need to consider missing info: reliability for A, D? No explicit. Could ask others if they have any reliability info for A or D. But we have already asked about reliability for A earlier? Not yet. In round 1, Agent 2 asked about reliability for A and got answer: no explicit info. So we have that. For D reliability? Not explicit. Could ask if any reliability info for D. But we have \"takes responsibility seriously\" which suggests reliability but not explicit. Could ask if any reliability info for D. But maybe not needed.\n\nWe need to produce final public message with reasoning and vote. Likely vote Candidate C as others. Provide summary and maybe ask if any other agent has any positive teamwork info for B or D. But we already asked and got none. Could ask if any agent has any reliability info for A or D. Already asked for A reliability, got none. For D reliability, not asked. Could ask: \"Do you have any information on Candidate D's reliability or track record of responsibility?\" But we have \"takes responsibility seriously\" which is responsibility. But reliability not explicit. Might ask anyway.\n\nBut the instruction: \"When reading the discussion history, if you see a question another agent asked that you can answer from your own information, include that answer in your public contribution \u2014 even if you were not directly asked.\" We have answered the question about D's teamwork earlier (we asked agent_2, got answer). So we can include that answer in our public message? Probably not needed, but we can reference that we have no teamwork info for D.\n\nNow produce public message: summarize each candidate, weigh, note missing info, ask if any agent has any positive teamwork/communication info for B or D, and vote for C.\n\nLet's do that."}
